Discussion. There is a large amount of color and size variation in this species. In Texas, collection records show an enormous discrepancy in size ( Fig. 7D, E ), while in Florida, color varies to a large degree ( Fig. 7 H–J), and in Mexico , specimens have a slightly different head shape; however, despite this, all molecularly sampled specimens came out in a single highly-supported clade with little genetic variation (
Baker et al . 2020
).
